{{wiktionary|crank|cranks}}
'''Crank''' may refer to:

{{tocright}}
==Mechanism==
* [[Crank (mechanism)]], in mechanical engineering, a bent portion of an axle, or shaft, or an arm keyed at right angles to the end of a shaft, by which motion is imparted to or received from it
* [[Crankset]], the component of a bicycle drivetrain that converts the reciprocating motion of the rider's legs into rotational motion
* [[Crankshaft]], the part of a piston engine which translates reciprocating linear piston motion into rotation

==Places==
* [[Crank, Merseyside]], a village near Rainford, England
* [[Cranks, Kentucky]]

==Popular culture==
* [[Crank (film)|''Crank'' (film)]], a 2006 film starring Jason Statham
** ''[[Crank: High Voltage]]'', the 2009 sequel
* [[Crank (Hoodoo Gurus album)|''Crank'' (Hoodoo Gurus album)]], 1994
* [[Crank (novel)|''Crank'' (novel)]], a 2004 book written by Ellen Hopkins
* [[Crank (song)|"Crank" (song)]], a 1993 song by the alternative rock band Catherine Wheel
* [[Crank (soundtrack)|''Crank'' (soundtrack)]]
* [[Crank (The Almighty album)|''Crank'' (The Almighty album)]], the fourth studio album released by Scottish heavy metal band The Almighty
* [[Crank! Records]], a record label that released albums by indie bands Mineral, The Gloria Record, and Bright Eyes
* Crank City, a 2012 album and song by Hank Pine and Lily Fawn

==Slang==
* [[Crank (person)]], a pejorative term for an annoyingly eccentric person
* [[Prank call]] or crank call, a false telephone call
* Crank, slang term for powdered [[substituted amphetamine]]s, especially [[methamphetamine]]

==Other uses==
* [[Crank (surname)]]
* [[Crank conjecture]], a term coined by Freeman Dyson to explain congruence patterns in integer partitions
* [[Cranks restaurant]], a chain of English wholefood vegetarian restaurants
* [[Crank ships]], a condition in which a ship becomes when it heels abnormally, and recovers slowly under the action of the wind
* [[Crank (number theory)]], of a partition of an integer is a certain integer associated with the partition

